gomodel:SYNGO_3855  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3: \"Pyk2 localization and dendritic spine density and morphology in Pyk2-deficient mice\"\n- \"Pyk2 immunofluorescence in the neuropil was punctate and appeared to surround MAP2-positive dendritic processes (Fig. 3a). Some Pyk2-positive puncta co-localized with PSD-95-positive puncta, identifying them as PSDs (Fig. 3b).\"\n- \"We then examined Pyk2 immunoreactivity by electron microscopy. Pyk2-positive immunogold particles were found in both presynaptic elements and dendritic spines (Fig. 3c and Supplementary Fig. 3a). Pyk2 was enriched in asymmetric (presumably excitatory) synapses as compared to symmetric (presumably inhibitory) synapses (Supplementary Fig. 3a-d).\". Experimental description: - \"Mice were anaesthetized (pentobarbital, 60 mg kg-1 i.p.) and intracardially perfused ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-07-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3855" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

